OL,3,CMan jailed for 'monstrous evil' attack
OL,4,Cthat has left baby profoundly disabled
OL,6,FThe jury convicted Kember of causing
OL,7,Fgrievous bodily harm with intent to
OL,8,Fthe baby, while Reilly was convicted
OL,9,Fof child cruelty.
OL,11,FJudge Julian Lambert jailed Kember for
OL,12,F21 years with a further four years on
OL,13,Fextended licence. He told Kember that
OL,14,Fhe will be required to serve two-
OL,15,Fthirds of that term behind bars and
OL,16,Fthat his release will then at the
OL,17,Fdiscretion of a parole board.
OL,19,FJudge: Kember's assault led to an
OL,20,F'utterly catastrophic, traumatic brain
OL,21,Finjury'
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/13
