OL,6,FKember was being transported to
OL,7,Fcustody in a police car travelling on
OL,8,Fthe motorway at 70mph when he grabbed
OL,9,Fthe steering wheel, causing the
OL,10,Fvehicle to veer across the carriageway.
OL,12,FThe judge told Kember this, as well as
OL,13,Fthreatening police officers during his
OL,14,Ftrial, illustrated the defendant's
OL,15,F"rage and dangerous loss of control",
OL,16,Fand found him dangerous ` resulting in
OL,17,Fthe extended sentence.
OL,19,FJudge: Reilly has shown 'no conscience
OL,20,Fand no regret for failing the child'
