OL,6,FProsecuting, Robin Shellard said the
OL,7,Finfant, now aged five, has been left
OL,8,Fnon-verbal, is registered blind,
OL,9,Fsuffers multiple daily seizures and
OL,10,Fhas other complex needs.
OL,12,F"All their difficulties are life-
OL,13,Flong," Mr Shellard said, adding that
OL,14,Fthe child has a reduced life
OL,15,Fexpectancy because of the conditions
OL,16,Fcaused by their injuries.
OL,18,F'They are in pain day and night' say
OL,19,Fadoptive family of baby
